items.title: Everything: A Tour of the Universe
items.headline: The Universe's Size, Shape and Structure - and Where We Fit In!
objectives_summary: Do you want to learn about the whole universe in one lesson? Did you know that only a hundred years ago we thought our Milky Way Galaxy was the entire universe? How much of the universe can we really see? Tour the universe with Home School Astronomy and get a sense of where we are located in the grand scheme of the universe and how big the universe really is.
Definition of the universe
Could there be more than one universe? Multiple Universes

items.title: Mars: The Haunting Red Planet
items.headline: Mars in our cultural lore and in our sights to explore
objectives_summary: Mars has long haunted mankind with its red glow and tantalizing proximity. Humans have known about Mars since before recorded history and almost all cultures named it after their gods of war because of its blood red color. Mars boasts a volcano so large that it peeks into space and a canyon so long that it looks like a scar on the planet even from Earth. Oh yea… and we’ll talk about Martians.
How did we discover Mars and why did most civilization name it after their god's of war?
How to observe Mars from Earth

items.title: The Ice Giants: Uranus & Neptune
items.headline: Twin Planets at the Edge of the Solar System
objectives_summary: There are giant planets of ice in the outer reaches of the solar system. Meet the planets our ancestors’ new nothing about – those you can’t spot in the sky without a telescope. Uranus and Neptune redefine violent weather, beauty and mystery.
Objective and Warm-up Activity
The Planets Uranus and Neptune and their place in the solar system

items.title: The Milky Way and Other Galaxies in the Universe
items.headline: A field guide to galactic structure, types and contents
objectives_summary: Our solar system is immense, but it gets lost in the vastness of our Milky Way Galaxy. Look at our place in the galaxy and our galaxy’s place in the universe. Examine the different kinds of galaxies including galaxy collisions and the black holes in the center.
Objective and Warm-up Activity
Perspective on Size and Distance
